these books, but the, there's this book called cognition in the wild that was really fascinating

00:20:16.219 --> 00:20:23.260
to me. And it's about the, it's about this idea that, um, people working together in a system

00:20:23.260 --> 00:20:29.579
can form this super brain and no one person in the system knows all of the parts, but together

00:20:30.219 --> 00:20:34.380
there are decision-making activities happening and there is value being created by,

00:20:34.380 --> 00:20:41.099
